.TH "btrfs_update_discard_index" 9 "btrfs_update_discard_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
btrfs_update_discard_index \- moves a block group along the discard lists
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" btrfs_update_discard_index
.BI "(struct btrfs_discard_ctl *discard_ctl "  ","
.BI "struct btrfs_block_group *block_group "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "discard_ctl" 12
discard control
.IP "block_group" 12
block_group of interest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Increment \fIblock_group\fP's discard_index.  If it falls of the list, let it be.
Otherwise add it back to the appropriate list.
